tions regarding \\\"Do not compile/run tests yourself,\\\" so I won't run gradle. The older Netty NioEventLoop class is public final, which is fine. I also need to think about the selector assertion and dynamic coverage. If that fails due to ClassNotFound on non-HotSpot, it wouldn't show coverage. I'll keep exploring whether the dynamic access report respects JVM arguments.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing JUnit and native image issues**\\n\\nI'm thinking they might run JUnit with JVM arguments from the test, which is good. I need to consider whether the build.gradle's agent buildArgs for add-opens will include the agent JVM. It looks like the tasks.withType(Test) does cover the Java agent. There could be an issue with the native-image and --add-opens for sun.nio.ch; it only opens the module to ALL-UNNAMED at build time, not at runtime. I’ll need to think about adding metadata for SelectorImpl fields to optimize the native image build. It's essential to ensure the fields are configured correctly to avoid missing registrations that could lead to errors down the line.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering metadata and test coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking that if the committed reachability metadata isn't updated, it's possible that tests pass because the native catches it. The \\\"dynamic-access coverage\\\" does track dynamic access call sites by executing tests under the agent without requiring metadata, which is good. I could update the metadata to include SelectorImpl fields and condition typeReached NioEventLoop to enhance library optimization under native. However, since the user specifically asked to improve test coverage, I need to be careful about implementing broad patches.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking metadata and commits**\\n\\nI'm looking into the test exercises and their dynamic access, which isn't represented in the metadata. It seems like there might not be an issue with the checkMetadataFiles. There's no requirement for all observed metadata to be committed. I need to commit, but I'm wondering about the `git status` — it might include other files that aren't supposed to be there. So, I need to make sure to use `git add` for just our files before committing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Qsd9riHmHZ3gklS1rLEmN6yl|fc_02f045514498a9d60169f0d069e31c8195bf334cf66e1f6f3a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git add tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/build.gradle tests/src/io.netty/netty-all/4.0.23.Final/src/test/java/io_netty/netty_all/NioEventLoopTest.java && git commit -m \"Add Netty NioEventLoop coverage test\"", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 710, "output": 658, "cacheRead": 41472, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42840, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777389659221, "responseId": "resp_02f045514498a9d60169f0d05bc8e08195abea11398e0187c1"}}
